    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To speed up your loan payoff, you need to stop the goblins from eating your lunch so aggressively. Here are a few ways to force more of your payment toward the principal:\n\n1.  **Make Extra Payments:** You can simply pay a lump sum toward the principal whenever you have extra cash. This immediately reduces the balance, which lowers the interest calculation for the next month. It's like telling the goblin, \"Stop hoarding gold, I'm taking the treasure chest away from you right now.\"\n\n2.  **Make Bi-Weekly Payments:** Instead of one big monthly payment, you can make two smaller payments every two weeks. This results in 26 payments a year instead of 12, which effectively adds an extra monthly payment to your schedule. This extra chunk hits the principal harder before the goblin can charge interest on it.\n\n3.  **Switch to a Bi-Weekly Schedule:** Some lenders allow you to switch your amortization schedule to bi-weekly. This automatically applies the extra payment logic without you having to manually calculate anything, though you still need to check if the goblin is happy with the new rhythm.\n\n4.  **Refinance to a Lower Rate:** If your current interest",
